 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0001-0001-0001-000000000001",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# IT Consulting Salary Analyser\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objective\n",
    "This notebook analyses a global IT job salary dataset (600+ records from Kaggle) to answer three practical questions:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Which job titles command the highest salaries?**\n",
    "2. **How does experience level affect compensation?**\n",
    "3. **Which countries pay data professionals the most?**\n",
    "\n",
    "The analysis follows a standard data pipeline: **Load → Clean → Analyse → Visualise → Findings**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0002-0002-0002-000000000002",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 1 · Import Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0003-0003-0003-000000000003",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Style settings for consistent, clean charts\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "plt.rcParams[\"figure.dpi\"] = 120"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0004-0004-0004-000000000004",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 2 · Load the Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "The CSV comes from [Kaggle – Data Science Salaries](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ruchi798/data-science-job-salaries).  \n",
    "Let's peek at the first few rows to understand the schema."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0005-0005-0005-000000000005",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv(\"data/ds_salaries.csv\")\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape: {df.shape[0]} rows × {df.shape[1]} columns\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0006-0006-0006-000000000006",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df.info()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0007-0007-0007-000000000007",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 3 · Data Cleaning\n",
    "\n",
    "Three quick fixes before analysis:\n",
    "1. Drop the auto-generated `Unnamed: 0` index column.  \n",
    "2. Map cryptic **experience-level** codes (`EN`, `MI`, `SE`, `EX`) to human-readable labels.  \n",
    "3. Map **employment-type** codes (`FT`, `PT`, `CT`, `FL`) similarly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0008-0008-0008-000000000008",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 1. Drop useless index column\n",
    "if \"Unnamed: 0\" in df.columns:\n",
    "    df = df.drop(columns=[\"Unnamed: 0\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Clean experience_level\n",
    "exp_map = {\n",
    "    \"EN\": \"Entry\",\n",
    "    \"MI\": \"Mid\",\n",
    "    \"SE\": \"Senior\",\n",
    "    \"EX\": \"Executive\",\n",
    "}\n",
    "df[\"experience_level\"] = df[\"experience_level\"].map(exp_map)\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3. Clean employment_type\n",
    "emp_map = {\n",
    "    \"FT\": \"Full-Time\",\n",
    "    \"PT\": \"Part-Time\",\n",
    "    \"CT\": \"Contract\",\n",
    "    \"FL\": \"Freelance\",\n",
    "}\n",
    "df[\"employment_type\"] = df[\"employment_type\"].map(emp_map)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Cleaned columns:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Experience levels : {df['experience_level'].unique().tolist()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Employment types  : {df['employment_type'].unique().tolist()}\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0009-0009-0009-000000000009",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Quick sanity check — no nulls should remain after mapping:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0010-0010-0010-000000000010",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df.isnull().sum()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0011-0011-0011-000000000011",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 4 · Exploratory Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4.1 Top 10 Highest-Paying Job Titles"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0012-0012-0012-000000000012",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "salary_by_role = (\n",
    "    df.groupby(\"job_title\")[\"salary_in_usd\"]\n",
    "    .mean()\n",
    "    .sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Top 10 Paying Roles (avg USD salary):\")\n",
    "salary_by_role.head(10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0013-0013-0013-000000000013",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.2 Salary by Experience Level"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0014-0014-0014-000000000014",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "salary_by_exp = (\n",
    "    df.groupby(\"experience_level\")[\"salary_in_usd\"]\n",
    "    .mean()\n",
    "    .sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Average salary by experience level:\")\n",
    "salary_by_exp"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0015-0015-0015-000000000015",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.3 Top 10 Highest-Paying Countries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0016-0016-0016-000000000016",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "salary_by_country = (\n",
    "    df.groupby(\"company_location\")[\"salary_in_usd\"]\n",
    "    .mean()\n",
    "    .sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Top 10 Paying Locations:\")\n",
    "salary_by_country.head(10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0017-0017-0017-000000000017",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 5 · Visualisations\n",
    "\n",
    "### 5.1 Top 10 Highest-Paying Roles"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0018-0018-0018-000000000018",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "top_roles = salary_by_role.head(10)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "sns.barplot(x=top_roles.values, y=top_roles.index, palette=\"viridis\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Top 10 Highest Paying Roles\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Average Salary (USD)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Job Role\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"charts/top_roles.png\", bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0019-0019-0019-000000000019",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5.2 Salary by Experience Level"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0020-0020-0020-000000000020",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))\n",
    "sns.barplot(x=salary_by_exp.index, y=salary_by_exp.values, palette=\"coolwarm\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Salary by Experience Level\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Experience Level\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Average Salary (USD)\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"charts/exp_level.png\", bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0021-0021-0021-000000000021",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5.3 Top 10 Highest-Paying Countries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0022-0022-0022-000000000022",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "top_countries = salary_by_country.head(10)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "sns.barplot(x=top_countries.values, y=top_countries.index, palette=\"magma\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Top Paying Countries\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Average Salary (USD)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Country\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"charts/countries.png\", bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0023-0023-0023-000000000023",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 6 · Key Findings\n",
    "\n",
    "| # | Insight | Detail |\n",
    "|---|---------|--------|\n",
    "| 1 | **Data Analytics Lead** is the highest-paying title on average. | Niche leadership roles command premium compensation because they sit at the intersection of technical execution and business strategy. |\n",
    "| 2 | **Executive > Senior > Mid > Entry** — experience level strongly correlates with salary. | The jump from Mid to Senior is the steepest, suggesting that companies reward depth of expertise and team leadership heavily. |\n",
    "| 3 | **The US dominates** salary levels, followed by Russia and New Zealand. | US salaries are inflated by high enterprise data-infrastructure budgets and intense competition for ML/Data Engineering talent. |\n",
    "| 4 | **ML & Data Engineering roles** show strong salary growth. | These roles directly influence scalable production systems and revenue-driving analytics, making them high-value hires. |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0024-0024-0024-000000000024",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 7 · Domain Perspective\n",
    "\n",
    "Having worked on IT consulting projects where I've seen hiring trends first-hand, these numbers match what I've observed in practice:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **ML Engineer salaries are rising fastest.** In recent years, hiring briefs I've come across have consistently prioritised ML Engineer and Data Engineer roles over traditional developer positions — this dataset confirms that trend quantitatively.\n",
    "- **The "Senior" jump is real.** Mid-level professionals often plateau until they can demonstrate ownership of end-to-end pipelines or models in production. The ~40 % salary gap between Mid and Senior levels in this data reflects that market reality.\n",
    "- **US-centric salary data can be misleading globally.** While US averages dominate, cost-of-living adjustments and purchasing-power parity would paint a more nuanced picture for candidates in India, Eastern Europe, or Southeast Asia. A useful extension of this project would be to normalise salaries by a PPP index.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Next steps:** Incorporate year-over-year trend analysis (`work_year` column) and remote-vs-onsite salary comparisons (`remote_ratio`) to build a more complete picture."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b0c1d0-0025-0025-0025-000000000025",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "*Notebook by Subrata — Project 1A: IT Salary Analyser*"
   ]
  }
